# CodeDNA v0.5

This project uses CodeDNA. Every Python file begins with a module docstring.

On EDIT:
- Re-read `rules:` before writing any logic
- Read `deps:` before changing function signatures
- Read `Depends:` / `Rules:` in function docstrings before writing logic there
- Apply `Modifies:` cascade targets in the same edit session

On CREATE:
- Write module docstring before any imports (deps/exports/used_by/tables/rules)
- For cross-file functions: add Google-style docstring with Depends: and Rules:
- At dangerous calls: add inline comment # includes X — filter Y below
- Use semantic naming: list_dict_users_from_db = get_users()

`exports:` are contracts — never rename without explicit instruction and updating all `used_by:` callers.

Module docstring format:
"""filename.py — <purpose ≤15 words>.

deps:    file.py → symbol | none
exports: fn(args) -> type
used_by: consumer.py → fn
tables:  table(col) | none
rules:   <hard constraint>
"""
